Package: snirh.lab
Type: Package
Title: Converts a data.frame to the Portuguese Information System for Water Resources (SNIRH) file format
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2025-09-20
Author: Luís Pereira
Authors@R: c(person("Luís", "Pereira", , "d57177@alunos.uevora.pt", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0628-4847")))
Description: Converts laboratory analytical data to SNIRH (Sistema Nacional de 
    Informação de Recursos Hídricos) (https://snirh.apambiente.pt) import format.
    The package handles data validation, unit conversions, station validation 
    against the SNIRH database, and formatting according to Portuguese national
    water monitoring standards. Supports surface water, groundwater, biota,
    and sediment data matrices with comprehensive quality control and error handling.
    The data table to import should include the following columns, in this exact order:
    'snirh_entity', 'snirh_site', 'snirh_id', 'sampling_date', 'value', and 'unit'.
    All columns must be of type character, except for 'sampling_date',
    which should be in a valid datetime format.
